During this security audit, I identified several cybersecurity risks in my daily digital habits. Although I use strong passwords, I realized that enabling Multi-Factor Authentication on all accounts is essential. I also discovered that regularly updating devices and reviewing account security settings greatly improves protection against cyber threats.

The most important improvement I will implement immediately is enabling MFA on every important account and reviewing password strength regularly. I will also avoid clicking suspicious links, verify email senders carefully and keep my system updated with the latest security patches.

Cybersecurity is extremely important in today's digital world because people rely heavily on technology for communication, education, banking and business activities. A single security mistake can result in data theft, financial loss or privacy violations. Therefore, developing good cyber hygiene and secure online habits is necessary for everyone. This assignment helped me understand that cybersecurity starts with securing ourselves before securing systems and networks.

